<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/21965967-amber"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1449092263i/21965967._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/21965967-amber">Amber</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes, it is an allusion to Pandora&apos;s Box. Pandora was given a jar as a gift and told never to open it. Naturally, being a human being, she was curious <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes, it is an allusion to Pandora's Box. Pandora was given a jar as a gift and told never to open it. Naturally, being a human being, she was curious and she opened it anyway, and as a result, unleashed evil into the world. <br /><br />In this story, the metaphorical "box" is a star, and the title of the book is a pretty strong foreshadowing that something bad is going to happen when curious humans explore the star and start messing around with what they find there.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link68433" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=68433&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F183902-i-just-finished-this-and-i-m-now-reading%2Fanswers%2F68433-yes-it-is-an-allusion">flag</a>
</div>
