<span id="freeTextContainer5618792855371405067">First of all, let&apos;s get all the bad things about this book out of the way. Um... let&apos;s see. It&apos;s really, <i>really</i> thick. Oh, and it has a cliffhanger ending, because of the sequel. Um... surely there must be something else I can come up with? <br/><br/>Now, the <b>good</b>: and, boy, there is a lot of that. This novel reads like a <i>greatest hits</i> of everything that is cool about science fiction. Yes, it is a massive book, but that&apos;s because it&apos;s filled with all kinds of goodies. You want it? It&apos;s probably here. It a</span>
  <span id="freeText5618792855371405067" style="display:none">First of all, let's get all the bad things about this book out of the way. Um... let's see. It's really, <i>really</i> thick. Oh, and it has a cliffhanger ending, because of the sequel. Um... surely there must be something else I can come up with? <br /><br />Now, the <b>good</b>: and, boy, there is a lot of that. This novel reads like a <i>greatest hits</i> of everything that is cool about science fiction. Yes, it is a massive book, but that's because it's filled with all kinds of goodies. You want it? It's probably here. It actually reads faster than you might suspect too, mainly because it's paced so evenly. Even when the chapters of exposition started, I was glued to the pages. <br />There is a <i>lot</i> going on here.<br /><br />This is probably the shortest review I've written. Which is ironic, considering the size of the novel concerned, but I don't have time to linger, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/45244.Judas_Unchained__Commonwealth_Saga___2_" title="Judas Unchained (Commonwealth Saga, #2) by Peter F. Hamilton" rel="nofollow noopener">Judas Unchained</a> isn't going to read itself.</span>
