    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_793379325" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/793379325" />
    <a title="Dara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13656026-dara"><img alt="Dara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1500476380p2/13656026.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/793379325?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dara" href="/user/show/13656026-dara">Dara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6136470-pandora-s-star">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13656026-dara?shelf=read-2014">read-2014</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13656026-dara?shelf=lady-protag">lady-protag</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13656026-dara?shelf=series">series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13656026-dara?shelf=scifi">scifi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13656026-dara?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13656026-dara?shelf=space-opera">space-opera</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer793379325" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15917707125809129188">At 1,144 pages, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/45252.Pandora_s_Star' title='Pandora&apos;s Star by Peter F. Hamilton' rel='nofollow noopener'>Pandora&apos;s Star</a> by <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/25375.Peter_F__Hamilton' title='Peter F. Hamilton' rel='nofollow noopener'>Peter F. Hamilton</a> is not a casual read. Hamilton uses all of those pages to create a rich and detailed future of the human race. Entertaining, frustrating, and exhilarating, Pandora&apos;s Star slowly pulls the reader into it&apos;s grasp and doesn&apos;t let go.<br/><br/><i>Pandora&apos;s Star</i> has a lot of characters and plenty of points-of-view, making it a little daunting at first. That said, Hamilton does a great job of making each character distinct and interesting. Even characters I initi</span>
  <span id="freeText15917707125809129188" style="display:none">At 1,144 pages, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/45252.Pandora_s_Star" title="Pandora's Star by Peter F. Hamilton" rel="nofollow noopener">Pandora's Star</a> by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/25375.Peter_F__Hamilton" title="Peter F. Hamilton" rel="nofollow noopener">Peter F. Hamilton</a> is not a casual read. Hamilton uses all of those pages to create a rich and detailed future of the human race. Entertaining, frustrating, and exhilarating, Pandora's Star slowly pulls the reader into it's grasp and doesn't let go.<br /><br /><i>Pandora's Star</i> has a lot of characters and plenty of points-of-view, making it a little daunting at first. That said, Hamilton does a great job of making each character distinct and interesting. Even characters I initially didn't like, I ended up excited to read about them and caring about their fates by the end of the novel.<br /><br />The plot starts with a pair of stars disappearing behind a massive barrier. Naturally, humans must go poke at it. The main plot involving the disappearance didn't click for me until about half-way through. There are other plot threads which start to connect and interweave in ways that aren't entirely clear yet but this is the first book in a rather large duology.<br /><br />There's a lot of world-building done in the best way: showing and not telling. Hamilton shows the readers through his character's eyes how the Commonwealth operates. We learn about their technology, history, culture, and different ways of life through experiences with the characters.<br /><br />In the Commonwealth, humans don't really die anymore. There's a process called rejuvenation where people go for a new, young version of their body when they reach a certain age and then are young again. I would have liked to know a bit more about the process but Hamilton doesn't delve into the science of how it works.<br /><br />The plot really picks up around the half-way mark. The first half is a lot of setup and character introduction. We meet the main players of the Dynasty families who have enormous amounts of wealth and power such as Nigel Sheldon, Ozzie Issacs, and the Burnelli family, investigator Paula Myo, Admiral Wilson Kime, and reporter Mellanie Rescorai. This builds a great foundation for the story but at times really drags on and becomes tedious.<br /><br />The characters are mostly all human but aliens are present in Hamilton's universe. There is a race called the Silfen which are almost like space elves. They're rather mystical but also quite frightening. The alien species play a larger part in the sequel, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/45244.Judas_Unchained" title="Judas Unchained by Peter F. Hamilton" rel="nofollow noopener">Judas Unchained</a>.<br /><br />The book ends on a riveting cliffhanger which I will not spoil here. Needless to say, it prompted me to immediately pick up the second novel.<br /><br /><i>Pandora's Star</i> is a slow burn of a book with fascinating characters, interesting storylines, and a deep and substantial world. Any sci-fi fan would be doing themselves a service by picking this up.<br /><br /><b>B</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="15917707125809129188" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


